== History == == Overview == The founding date of the shrine is unknown. During the {{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代|12=draft}}, it was known as Mikuchi Myōjin (水口明神) or Hakusan Daigongen (白山大権現) and also worshipped {{ill|Gozu Tennō|ja|牛頭天王|1=Gozu Tennō|1=Gozu Tennō|12=draft}} as Wakamiya (young deity).
The shrine's associated temple ({{ill|Jingū-ji|ja|神宮寺|12=draft}}) was abolished in {{ill|Meiji 40|ja|明治40th year|12=draft}} (1907).
=== type === * {{ill|Ten'an|ja|天安|12=draft}} 3rd year (859), January 27: Elevated to the rank of Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade (正五位下) as per the {{ill|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|ja|日本三代実録|12=draft}}. The shrine is referred to as "Tsuge Yamaguchi Shrine" in the text. == See Also == * {{ill|List of Shikinaisha shrines in Yamato Province|ja|Yamato Province の式内社一覧|12=draft}}
