== Enshrined Deities == The shrine primarily enshrines {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|ja|大山祇神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamatsumi|qq=}}, with {{ill|Kukunochi|ja|久久迩知命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kukunochi|qq=}} and {{ill|Haniyasu-hiko and Haniyasu-hime|lt=Haniyasu-hiko and Haniyasu-hime|lt=Haniyasu|ja|波爾夜須命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Haniyasu|qq=}} as additional deities.
== History == == Overview == The founding date of the shrine is unknown. During the {{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Edo period|qq=}}, it was known as Mikuchi Myōjin (水口明神) or Hakusan Daigongen (白山大権現) and also worshipped {{ill|Gozu Tennō|ja|牛頭天王|1=Gozu Tennō|1=Gozu Tennō|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gozu Tennō|13=User:Immanuelle/Gozu Tennō|qq=}} as Wakamiya (young deity).
The shrine's associated temple ({{ill|Jingū-ji|ja|神宮寺|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jingū-ji|qq=}}) was abolished in {{ill|Meiji 40|ja|明治40th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji 40|qq=}} (1907).
=== type === * {{ill|Ten'an|ja|天安|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ten'an|qq=}} 3rd year (859), January 27: Elevated to the Rank of Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade (正五位下) as per the {{ill|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|ja|日本三代実録|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|qq=}}. The shrine is referred to as "Tsuge Yamaguchi Shrine" in the text. == See Also == * {{ill|List of Shikinaisha in Yamato Province|ja|Yamato Province の式内社一覧|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/List of Shikinaisha in Yamato Province|qq=}}
