== Enshrined Deities == The shrine primarily enshrines {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|ja|大山祇神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamatsumi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to オオヤマツミ}}, with {{ill|Kukunochi|ja|久久迩知命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kukunochi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} and {{ill|Haniyasu-hiko and Haniyasu-hime|lt=Haniyasu-hiko and Haniyasu-hime|lt=Haniyasu|ja|波爾夜須命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Haniyasu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} as additional deities.
== History == == Overview == The founding date of the shrine is unknown. During the [[:en:Edo period|Edo period]], it was known as Mikuchi Myōjin (水口明神) or Hakusan Daigongen (白山大権現) and also worshipped [[:en:Gozu Tennō|Gozu Tennō]] as Wakamiya (young deity).
The shrine's associated temple ([[:en:Jingū-ji|Jingū-ji]]) was abolished in {{ill|Meiji 40|ja|明治40年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji 40|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1907年|1=1907|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q2048}} (1907).
=== type === * {{ill|Ten'an|ja|天安|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ten'an|qq=|1=Cheonan|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q3577288}} 3rd year (859), January 27: Elevated to the Rank of Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade (正五位下) as per the [[:en:Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku]]. The shrine is referred to as "Tsuge Yamaguchi Shrine" in the text. == See Also == * {{ill|List of Shikinaisha in Yamato Province|ja|Yamato Province の式内社一覧|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/List of Shikinaisha in Yamato Province|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}
